---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ScrollReveal from "../components/ScrollReveal.tsx";
import { SITE } from "../config/site.mjs";
---

<Layout
	title={`About | ${SITE.title}`}
	description="My background, my approach and why I started Silverbeet Technology"
	canonicalURL={`${SITE.url}/about`}
>
	<Header />
	<main id="main-content" role="main">
		<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-20">
			<ScrollReveal client:idle>
				<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">About</h1>
			</ScrollReveal>
			<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.1}>
				<p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-12">
					My background, my approach and why I started Silverbeet Technology
				</p>
			</ScrollReveal>

			<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
				<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
					<h2>Overview</h2>
					<p>
						For over 25 years, I’ve made technology work for people — from
						helping users troubleshoot desktops, to building infrastructure for
						development teams to collaborate and write code. Securing networks
						and building architecting reliable systems that scale. I founded
						Silverbeet Technology to bring principled, practical tech solutions
						to individuals and small businesses who want their technology to
						just work, without unnecessary complexity.
					</p>
				</ScrollReveal>

				<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
					<h3>My background spans</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>
							My early IT years dealt with supporting users with their desktops,
							followed by learning end-to-end networking configuration, followed
							by understanding and running the servers
						</li>
						<li>
							Deep experience and a strong interest, in open source software and
							Linux while helped me understand the shift and new world those
							ideals provided. I've been that that path ever since
						</li>
						<li>
							DevOps, automation, and reproducible infrastructure, sharing my
							ideas to utilize reliable tools that follow best practices
						</li>
						<li>
							I've given talks, shared technical presentations and
							security-focused research, including talks at infosec conferences
							such as DEF CON and BSidesLV. I've written position papers dealing
							with sustainable server architecture for biodiversity data
						</li>
					</ul>
					<p>
						I believe in making tech understandable, dependable, and secure —
						whether that means optimizing a server stack, hardening a service,
						or automating a build pipeline, all while being open and transparent
						with my approaches, and sharing details and documentation of the
						solutions I've built
					</p>
				</ScrollReveal>

				<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
					<h3>What drives me</h3>
					<p>
						From the moment I discovered open source in 1999, I’ve been
						passionate about software freedom, community-driven tools, and
						solutions that empower users. That curiosity turned into a career in
						helping people solve real tech challenges.
					</p>
				</ScrollReveal>

				<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
					<h3>My approach</h3>
					<p>
						Rather than pushing expensive, proprietary software or complex tools
						for their own sake, I focus on:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<ol>
							✔ Using open source and proven DevOps practices where applicable
						</ol>
						<ol>
							✔ Automating builds and deployments for reliability and
							reproducibility
						</ol>
						<ol>✔ Making systems secure by design — not by accident</ol>
						<ol>✔ Helping clients decide when to buy vs build</ol>
					</ul>
					<p>
						If you’re looking for straightforward but powerful IT and security
						solutions with the future in mind — I’m here to talk about what will
						work best to achieve your goals. Feel free to
						<a
							href="/contact/"
							class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
							>contact</a
						> me to start a dialog.
					</p>
				</ScrollReveal>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</Layout>
